And OK check- did that. But ideally,you want to do it every day.
好的 做过了 但最理想的是每天做

100
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,520
Because by doing it every day,that's when you form a habit.
因为每天去做才能养成习惯

101
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:18,380
That's when you transform your thinking.
那样才能改变思维

102
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,630
And if you do it every day,the key is to vary,
每天去做的话 关健是要有变化

103
00:06:20,850 --> 00:06:23,250
to think about different aspect every day,
每天思考不同的方向

104
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:26,130
to think about different aspects of your family
思考家人的不同方面

105
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:28,140
if you write family every day.
如果你每天都给家人写信

106
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:31,200
To write about work one week. To write about home the next week.
一周讲述工作 下一周写家庭

107
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,730
Maintaining mindfulness,
每次都要用心

108
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:37,380
focusing on things you didn't notice before,
专注以前没有注意过的事情

109
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:40,600
creating novel distinctions,as Ellen Langer would say.
发现新的特点 Ellen Langer如是说

110
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:42,000
And visualize-
并在脑中想像

111
00:06:42,190 --> 00:06:45,200
so when you are thinking about your girlfriend or boyfriend,
当你想到你的女或男朋友

112
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:48,430
and writting your gratitude,visualize them.
书写感激之情时 在脑海中想像他们

113
00:06:48,690 --> 00:06:50,750
When you are thinking about the meal
当你想到

114
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:54,790
that you just had in your dinning hall which was delicious,
刚在食堂吃过的一顿美味可口的饭时

115
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,340
think about it. Visualize it. Make it as real as possible.
想它 在脑海中想像 让它变得尽可能真实

116
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,030
That's how children think.
孩子就是这样思考

117
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,640
And that's why children have this freshness on the day to day-
所以孩子们每天都感觉新鲜

118
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:08,170
they don't take anything for granted. They see life as a miracle.
他们不把任何东西视为理所当然 他们视生命为奇迹

119
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:11,200
You know,Emerson once said,
爱默生曾经说过

120
00:07:11,970 --> 00:07:16,060
"if the stars would shine once in a thousand years,
"如果星星每千年闪烁一次

121
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:21,510
we would all look up and praise the glory of this world.
我们都会仰视赞美这个世界的美丽

122
00:07:22,170 --> 00:07:26,040
But because they shine every day,we take them for granted."
但是因为它们每天都在闪烁 我们将之视为理所当然"

123
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:27,690
For children,that dosen't exist.
在孩子眼中不存在理所当然

124
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:28,460
And part of the reason why it dosen't exist
其中的一个原因

125
00:07:28,650 --> 00:07:32,410
is that because they don't think automatically,conceptually.
是因为他们不会自动地概念性地思考

126
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:36,790
They think more perceptually. Or sensually.
他们的思维是感知感性的

127
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:40,770
And they remain connected to the real.
他们和现实保持联系

128
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,200
And we can do it simply by visualizing.
通过在脑海中想像 我们就能做到

129
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:45,000
This is a wonderful research done here,
这项杰出研究完成于这里

130
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:47,500
William James Hall,8th floor.
