whether it's to your 1st grade teacher. Just do it.
或是一年级老师 去做吧

305
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:13,010
Whether it's to your coach. The largest largest peak,boost,
或者是对你们的教练 表达感激时

306
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:16,340
spike in wellbeing when we are expressing gratitude to others.
是最让我们感到幸福的时候

307
00:17:16,730 --> 00:17:18,650
Quite remarkable if you think about it.
想想吧 相当不可思议

308
00:17:19,110 --> 00:17:21,890
And if you think about it further,it is a win-win.
进一步思考会发现它是双赢的

309
00:17:22,150 --> 00:17:24,690
Because obviously you get the benefit-
因为显然你从中得益

310
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:28,500
this is what the research shows. We feel good when we express it.
研究已证明了这一点 表达感激时我们感觉很好

311
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:32,000
and the other person feels good too. They benefit a great deal.
对方也会感觉很好 他们的获益良多

312
00:17:32,210 --> 00:17:34,560
So you are creating a win-win and an upward spiral,because
于是你创造了一个双赢的局面 一个上升的螺旋

313
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:38,920
that person is then more likely to express gratitude to others.
因为对方也更可能向他人表达感激

314
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,700
The best way to lead it by an example:
最好的方法是以身作则

315
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:44,170
be the change you want to see in the world,as Ghandi said.
成为你期许见到的改变 如甘地所说

316
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,760
So you want people to be more grateful?
想让他人充满感激?

317
00:17:45,990 --> 00:17:47,810
Express gratitude yourself.
先以身作则表达感激

318
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,650
They are more likely to then take it on
他们才可能承接下去

319
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:52,600
and express gratitude to others. So not only you
向他人表达感激 你不仅仅

320
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,270
start an upward spiral between you and that person,
在你和对方之间启动了一个上行螺旋

321
00:17:56,690 --> 00:18:00,170
but also potentially between that person as well as others.
对方和他人之间可以承接上行

322
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,540
Paying it forward. Paying it forward.
传递出去 传递出去

323
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,870
The downside of this intervention is
这种干预的不利之处是

